=== Assignment ===

# How would you assign the value 3.14 to a variable called pi?
# Is it possible to assign an ''int'' to a ''double''?  
## Is the reverse possible?

{{Solution|title=Solution|text=
* The standard way of assigning 3.14 to pi is: 
<source lang="C">
double pi;
pi = 3.14;
</source>
** Since pi is a constant, good programming convention dictates to make it unchangeable during runtime. Extra credit if you use one of the following two lines:
<source lang="C">
const float pi = 3.14;
#define pi 3.14
</source>
* Yes, for example :
<source lang="C">
int a = 67;
double b;
b = a;
</source>
* Yes, but a cast is necessary and the double is truncated:
<source lang="C">
double a=89;
int b;
b = (int) a;
</source>

